|13,74
     The Set_Attr procedure is used to set terminal attributes when your
program is writing output.  The argument of Set_Attr is an integer
indicating the attribute you want to set (colour, bold face, reverse video,
etc.).  The currently recognized values are

     0 - normal roman letters
     1 - bold-face
     2 - italics
     4 - reverse video
     8 - solid underline
     16 - dotted underline
     24 - dashed underline
